    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "### Feature already in Vim?\r\n\r\nYes\r\n\r\n### Feature description\r\n\r\nCurrently Replace mode pasting is implemented using `nvim_buf_set_lines()`. This approach has several problems:\r\n- Its code looks ugly.\r\n- It doesn't deal with multibyte characters well.\r\n- It is hard to support streamed pasting.\r\n- It is hard to support Virtual Replace mode.\r\n\r\nAn alternative approach may be to use `nvim_input()` or `nvim_feedkeys()` with the `'paste'` option set. This approach may be slower, but I don't think it is common for one to paste a very large block of text in Replace mode.",
    "closed_at": null,
    "closed_by": null,
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "The same problem mentioned in #17724 needs to be considered when setting the `'paste'` option though. Using `nvim_feedkeys()` still requires setting the `'paste'` option because some things can only be disabled using the `'paste'` option in Replace mode.",
